  "text": "The Kubernetes API deprecation policy enforcement is implemented through a coordinated system across multiple components in kubernetes/kubernetes repository:\n\n## Core Deprecation Detection and Warning Generation\n\n**staging/src/k8s.io/apiserver/pkg/endpoints/deprecation/deprecation.go** (lines 29-135) is the foundational file that implements API deprecation policy enforcement. It defines three key interfaces:\n- `apiLifecycleDeprecated`: Interface for types that implement APILifecycleDeprecated() method returning major/minor version\n- `apiLifecycleRemoved`: Interface for types that implement APILifecycleRemoved() method returning removal version\n- `apiLifecycleReplacement`: Interface for types that implement APILifecycleReplacement() method returning replacement GVK\n\nThree critical functions implement the deprecation policy:\n1. `IsDeprecated(obj runtime.Object, currentMajor, currentMinor int)` (lines 61-86): Checks if an API object is deprecated by comparing its deprecation version with the current server version\n2. `RemovedRelease(obj runtime.Object)` (lines 88-98): Returns the major.minor version string when an API will be removed (e.g., \"1.22\")\n3. `WarningMessage(obj runtime.Object)` (lines 100-134): Generates human-readable deprecation warnings including deprecated version, removal version, and replacement API\n4. `MajorMinor(v version.Info)` (lines 44-59): Parses version strings to extract major/minor components\n\n## Warning Injection Handler\n\n**staging/src/k8s.io/apiserver/pkg/endpoints/warning/warning.go** (lines 25-39) implements `AddWarningsHandler()` which wraps HTTP handlers to inject deprecation warnings into response headers via the warning context.\n\n## API Server Route Installation and Integration\n\n**staging/src/k8s.io/apiserver/pkg/endpoints/installer.go** (lines 781-930) integrates deprecation policy enforcement into the API server. The `installResourceHandlers()` function:\n- Creates a versioned copy of API types (line 789)\n- Calls `deprecation.MajorMinor(versioninfo.Get())` to get current server version (line 791)\n- Calls `deprecation.IsDeprecated()` to check if API is deprecated (line 792)\n- If deprecated, calls `deprecation.RemovedRelease()` to get removal version (line 794)\n- Calls `deprecation.WarningMessage()` to generate warnings (line 795)\n- Wraps each HTTP handler with `utilwarning.AddWarningsHandler()` to inject warnings (lines 814, 840, 873, 905, 930)\n- Passes deprecated flag and removedRelease to metrics instrumentation\n\n## Metrics Recording and Audit Annotations\n\n**staging/src/k8s.io/apiserver/pkg/endpoints/metrics/metrics.go** (lines 377-385, 581-606) records deprecation metrics and audit annotations:\n- `deprecatedAnnotationKey = \"k8s.io/deprecated\"`: Audit annotation set to \"true\" for deprecated API requests\n- `removedReleaseAnnotationKey = \"k8s.io/removed-release\"`: Audit annotation set to removal version string\n- `MonitorRequest()` (lines 581-620): Records deprecated API requests in `deprecatedRequestGauge` metric with labels including removal version, and adds audit annotations via `audit.AddAuditAnnotation()`\n\n## Custom Resource Definition Deprecation Support\n\n**staging/src/k8s.io/apiextensions-apiserver/pkg/apiserver/customresource_handler.go** (lines 1042-1049, 1150-1162) implements CRD version deprecation:\n- Checks `v.Deprecated` field on CustomResourceDefinitionVersion (line 1042)\n- If deprecated, uses custom `v.DeprecationWarning` or generates default warning via `defaultDeprecationWarning()` (lines 1044-1048)\n- `defaultDeprecationWarning()` (lines 1150-1162): Generates CRD-specific deprecation messages recommending newer served versions\n\n## Code Generation for Lifecycle Methods\n\n**staging/src/k8s.io/code-generator/cmd/prerelease-lifecycle-gen/main.go** and **status.go** (lines 483-491) implement the code generator that:\n- Processes `+k8s:prerelease-lifecycle-gen:deprecated=<major>.<minor>` tags on types\n- Processes `+k8s:prerelease-lifecycle-gen:removed=<major>.<minor>` tags on types\n- Processes `+k8s:prerelease-lifecycle-gen:replacement=<group>,<version>,<kind>` tags on types\n- Auto-generates APILifecycleDeprecated(), APILifecycleRemoved(), and APILifecycleReplacement() methods on affected types\n- Auto-generated methods produce zz_generated.prerelease-lifecycle.go files across the codebase\n\n## Enforcement Workflow\n\n1. API types define lifecycle information through build tags in their type definitions\n2. Code generator creates APILifecycleDeprecated(), APILifecycleRemoved(), and APILifecycleReplacement() methods\n3. When the API server starts, installer.go registers endpoints and checks deprecation status\n4. For each request to a deprecated API:\n   - deprecation.IsDeprecated() returns true\n   - deprecation.RemovedRelease() provides removal version\n   - deprecation.WarningMessage() generates user-facing warning\n   - AddWarningsHandler() injects warning into HTTP response headers\n   - MonitorRequest() records metrics and audit annotations\n5. Clients receive warnings in HTTP headers and administrators see metrics/audit logs\n\nThis multi-layer enforcement ensures deprecated APIs are clearly marked in responses, tracked in metrics, and audited, allowing operators to identify and migrate away from deprecated APIs before removal."
}

